{
  "doc_id": "44733",
  "text": "With respect to the spore hydrophobicity, a hydrophobicity value for Aspergillus spores of 89.3 ± 1.9% was obtained, which remained fairly constant for 9 days. A previous work reported the use of Streptomyces spores to destabilize petroleum distillate emulsions which presented a maximum hydrophobicity of 72% after 15 days [CITATION_1] .",
